result.execSummary:
The defendant Marion Romaine Bell-Wilson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Vehicle Operator Flee/Elude Officer, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(3).
  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

10:14 AM Prosecuting attorney Brenda L. Yaskal in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Marion Romaine Bell-Wilson in court.  Attorney Anthony C. Delyea in court for Marion Romaine Bell-Wilson. Attorney Delyea stated there is a new bail jumping charge that was filed this morning. They would like to resolve everything at one time. Attorney Yaskal stated it is not in this county. 10:15/11:17 Agreement recited by the State (now ADA Jordan Lippert). Court reviewed the rights & elements. Defendant pled guilty to counts 1 & 2 of the amended information. Court found defendant guilty, entered judgment. Sentencing statements. Court withheld sentence, on count 1 placed the defendant on probation for 2 years conditions of probation include: 90 days in jail, with Huber. $518.00 costs. Maintain absolute sobriety. Complete an AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment recommendations. 6 month DL revocation. Submit DNA sample. On Count 2, withheld sentence, placed the defendant on probation for 1 year. Conditions of probation include: $243.00 costs. Submit DNA sample. Any bond on hand will be applied towards costs. 7 days sentence credit.
